          "body": "Verse 10 is arguably the most theologically alarming sentence in the entire Books of Chronicles. Athaliah 'rose and destroyed all the royal offspring of the house of Judah.' The word 'all' is the horror. The Davidic covenant, sworn in 2 Samuel 7:12-16 and undergirding the entire theological architecture of Chronicles, rests on the continuation of the Davidic seed. In one sentence, Athaliah — a foreign-descended queen who has never belonged on David's throne — attempts to annihilate that seed completely. The Chronicler gives no theological comment here, unlike verse 7. He does not need to. The starkness of the sentence is its own commentary. Every reader who has followed the Davidic narrative from 1 Chronicles onward knows what is at stake. If all the royal seed is destroyed, God's covenant oath appears to fail."
